Follow the steps below to install the latest development version of mapa from GitHub (the script first installs BiocManager and remotes if you don’t have them):

if (!requireNamespace("BiocManager", quietly = TRUE)) {
 install.packages("BiocManager") 
}

if (!requireNamespace("remotes", quietly = TRUE)) {
 install.packages("remotes") 
}

remotes::install_github(
  "jaspershen-lab/mapa",
  dependencies = TRUE,
  repos = BiocManager::repositories(),
  upgrade = "ask"
)

Follow the steps below to install the latest development version of mapa shinyapp from GitHub (the script first installs BiocManager, remotes, and mapa if you don’t have them):

if (!requireNamespace("BiocManager", quietly = TRUE)) {
 install.packages("BiocManager") 
}

if (!requireNamespace("remotes", quietly = TRUE)) {
 install.packages("remotes") 
}

remotes::install_github(
  "jaspershen-lab/mapa",
  dependencies = TRUE,
  repos = BiocManager::repositories(),
  upgrade = "ask"
)

remotes::install_github(
  "jaspershen-lab/mapashiny",
  dependencies = TRUE,
  repos        = BiocManager::repositories(),
  upgrade      = "ask"
)
